<subSubSection pageId="67" pageNumber="68" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="67.[151,1437,1071,1710]" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">
Morphology. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[353,776,1107,1133]" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">D VI + I,13–16; A I,12–15; P 18–19</emphasis>
(Miller 1986). Moderately large goby with subcylindrical body, laterally compressed towards caudal fin, head moderately large. Snout large and blunt. Eyes dorsolateral, interorbital space narrow. Caudal peduncle deep, but lower than body depth. Dorsal fins of similar height, the first dorsal fin may be slightly higher, with more or less rounded edge and no elongate spines. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">Caudal fin slightly pointed, almost rounded.</emphasis>
Predorsal area and nape scaled (Miller 1986). 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">Scales large, visible on body and usually also on predorsal area.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="67.[151,1437,1071,1710]" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">
Live coloration. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">Body with 2 longitudinal rows of gray-brown to orange-brown spots, more or less overlaid with yellow or orange</emphasis>
, one row along back and another along lateral midline; smaller spots of the same color (and not lines) on head (
<figureCitation box="[368,452,1395,1421]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1061,1085]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1037]" captionTargetId="figure-19@22.[151,1436,181,1037]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 17. Live coloration in its natural habitat of Lesueurigobius friesii. Photo by R. Svensen, Stavanger, Norway." pageId="67" pageNumber="68">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="67" pageNumber="68">Both dorsal fins and upper half of caudal fin with yellow to orange spots; second dorsal-fin edge yellow to orange with a blue to whitish submarginal band</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Moen, F. E. &amp; Svensen, E." box="[1072,1345,1431,1457]" pageId="67" pageNumber="68" refId="ref61908" refString="Moen, F. E. &amp; Svensen, E. (2004) Marine fish and invertebrates of Northern Europe. KOM, Kristiansund / AquaPress, Southendon-Sea, Essex, 608 pp." type="book" year="2004">Moen &amp; Svensen 2004</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Louisy, P." pageId="67" pageNumber="68" refId="ref60639" refString="Louisy, P. (2015) Europe and Mediterranean Marine Fish Identification Guide. 3 rd Edition. Eugen Ulmer Ed., Paris, 512 pp." type="book" year="2015">Louisy 2015</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
